

Fjavac: a functional Java compiler

  http://www.cis.upenn.edu/~stse/javac/


Stephen Tse <stse@cis.upenn.edu>
2005-0517



** EXAMPLES

> emacs test.java
> make


** INSTALL

For fast OCaml compilation, use ocamlopt.opt (the native-code version
of the OCaml native-code compiler). If ocamlopt.opt is installed in
PATH, Makefile will use them by default. But Debian does not install
ocamlopt.opt, ocamlc.opt, or ocamllex.opt. Compile it yourself: do 
'make world.opt install' in an OCaml distribution.

Read README.fs for compiling fjavac with F# under Linux/Mono.


